BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Midsummer Night's Dream
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260711T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260711T214500
DTSTAMP:20260707T014648Z
UID:occ-778@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's forest comedy of runaway lovers\, amateur actors
 \, and fairies with a misapplied love potion.\n\nShakespeare's comedy of o
 ne moonlit night in the woods outside Athens. Four runaway lovers\, a band
  of amateur actors\, and a feuding fairy king and queen cross paths\, and 
 a mischievous sprite's love potion lands on the wrong eyelids. Before morn
 ing\, affections have swapped and the weaver Bottom is wearing a donkey's 
 head. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\, performed with food and drink
  served at the table in its Elizabethan-style playhouse.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T013014Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/a-midsummer-nights-
 dream
END:VEVENT
