BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Comedy of Errors
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260806T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260806T212000
DTSTAMP:20260707T014648Z
UID:occ-794@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's shortest\, most slapstick comedy: two sets of tw
 ins\, one city\, and mistaken identity run gloriously amok.\n\nShakespeare
 's shortest and most farcical play: two sets of identical twins\, separate
 d at birth as infants\, end up in the same city without knowing it\, and t
 he mistaken identities pile up into wrongful beatings\, an arrest\, and ac
 cusations of madness and demonic possession. Adam King directs for the Atl
 anta Shakespeare Company\, performed with the playhouse's table seating an
 d food and drink service. Part of a three-comedy repertory alongside The T
 aming of the Shrew and Twelfth Night\; performances run through September 
 5.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T013014Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/august-threepeat-sh
 rew-comedy-of-errors-and-twelfth-night-in-repertory
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Taming of the Shrew
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260807T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260807T215500
DTSTAMP:20260707T014648Z
UID:occ-801@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's battle-of-the-sexes comedy with an all-female+ c
 ast\, one of three comedies in an August repertory.\n\nHeadstrong Katherin
 e cannot marry off fast enough to suit her father\, and her younger sister
  cannot marry until she does. Enter Petruchio\, a bachelor as loud as Kath
 erine is sharp\, and the sparring begins. Whether the play's "taming" is c
 omedy or cruelty has been argued for centuries\; here an all-female+ cast\
 , directed by Rachel Frawley\, takes it on for the Atlanta Shakespeare Com
 pany. Part of an August repertory alternating three Shakespeare comedies\;
  this production runs through September 3.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T013014Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/august-threepeat-sh
 rew-comedy-of-errors-and-twelfth-night-in-repertory
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Twelfth Night
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260808T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260808T220500
DTSTAMP:20260707T014648Z
UID:occ-807@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's shipwreck comedy of twins\, disguise\, and yello
 w stockings\, in the Atlanta Shakespeare Company's three-comedy August rep
 ertory.\n\nShipwrecked on the coast of Illyria and believing her twin brot
 her drowned\, Viola disguises herself as a young man and enters Duke Orsin
 o's service\, promptly tangling herself into a love triangle. Meanwhile\, 
 a forged letter convinces the pompous steward Malvolio that yellow stockin
 gs are the way to his lady's heart. Mary Ruth Ralston directs for the Atla
 nta Shakespeare Company\, with dinner-table seating and drink service duri
 ng the show. Part of the August Threepeat\, a repertory rotating three Sha
 kespeare comedies nightly\; this one plays through September 4.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T013014Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/august-threepeat-sh
 rew-comedy-of-errors-and-twelfth-night-in-repertory
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Comedy of Errors
