DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260814T220500
DTSTAMP:20260707T014648Z
UID:occ-808@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's shipwreck comedy of twins\, disguise\, and yello
 w stockings\, in the Atlanta Shakespeare Company's three-comedy August rep
 ertory.\n\nShipwrecked on the coast of Illyria and believing her twin brot
 her drowned\, Viola disguises herself as a young man and enters Duke Orsin
 o's service\, promptly tangling herself into a love triangle. Meanwhile\, 
 a forged letter convinces the pompous steward Malvolio that yellow stockin
 gs are the way to his lady's heart. Mary Ruth Ralston directs for the Atla
 nta Shakespeare Company\, with dinner-table seating and drink service duri
 ng the show. Part of the August Threepeat\, a repertory rotating three Sha
 kespeare comedies nightly\; this one plays through September 4.
