BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mel Konner’s Sixteen Springs or Four Loves (Staged Reading)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261114T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261114T160000
DTSTAMP:20260707T014648Z
UID:occ-1494@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Staged Reading
DESCRIPTION:A book-in-hand reading of a new play filling in the sixteen mi
 ssing years of The Winter's Tale.\n\nAtlanta playwright Mel Konner imagine
 s what happens during the sixteen-year gap in Shakespeare's The Winter's T
 ale\, and this time Antigonus survives the bear. The abandoned babe\, here
  named Trouvita\, grows up smart and strong in a shepherd family\, while b
 ack in Sicilia a slandered queen and her mad king head toward very differe
 nt fates. A staged reading from the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\, ahead of
  a full production in Spring 2027.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T013014Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/mel-konner-s-sixtee
 n-springs-or-four-loves-staged-reading
END:VEVENT
